            <h3>Hypertension Medication</h3>
            <p>Hypertension medication controls high blood pressure by decreasing the pressure. This can be done by causing the body to remove excess water and salt from the blood to decrease the volume, relaxing rigid blood vessels, reducing the force of heartbeats or blocking nerve activity causing blood vessel rigidity.</p>
